requirements.contract:
Create class AirPurifier with the following interface:

        class AirPurifier:
            def __init__(self, device, index: int): ...

            @property
            def raw(self) -> dict:
                """Return the dict at ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_CONTROL[index]."""

            @property
            def mode(self) -> int:
                """Return value of ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_MODE ("5900")."""

            @property
            def air_quality(self) -> int:
                """Return value of ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_AIR_QUALITY ("5907")."""

            @property
            def fan_speed(self) -> int:
                """Return value of ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_FAN_SPEED ("5908")."""

            @property
            def controls_locked(self) -> bool:
                """Return True when ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_CONTROLS_LOCKED ("5905") is non-zero."""

            @property
            def leds_off(self) -> bool:
                """Return True when ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_LEDS_OFF ("5906") is non-zero."""

      For the AIR_PURIFIER fixture:
        raw["15025"][0]["5900"] == 1  → mode == 1
        raw["15025"][0]["5907"] == 5  → air_quality == 5
        raw["15025"][0]["5908"] == 10 → fan_speed == 10
        raw["15025"][0]["5905"] == 0  → controls_locked == False
        raw["15025"][0]["5906"] == 0  → leds_off == False

Create class AirPurifierControl with the following interface:

        class AirPurifierControl:
            def __init__(self, device): ...

            @property
            def raw(self) -> list:
                """Return device.raw[ATTR_AIR_PURIFIER_CONTROL]."""

            @property
            def air_purifiers(self) -> list[AirPurifier]:
                """Return one AirPurifier instance per entry in raw."""
